p-1 | k \Rightarrow k = (p-1) n
n \in \mathbb{N}
 1^{(p-1)^n} + 2 ^{(p-1)^n} + \cdots + (p-1)^{(p-1)^n} = \underbrace{1 + 1 + \cdots + 1}_{p-1}  = p-1 \equiv -1 \mod p.
k=1
1 + 2 + \cdots + (p-1)= \frac{(p-1)(p)}{2} \equiv 0 \mod p
k = n
1^n + 2^n + \cdots + (p-1)^n \equiv 0 \mod p
\mathbb{F}_p^*
\zeta
\zeta^{p-1}=1
\sum_{i=0}^{p-2} (\zeta^k)^i
p-1 | k
\sum_{i=0}^{p-2} 1 = p-1 = -1
\zeta^k \neq 1
\dfrac{{(\zeta^k})^{p-1} - 1}{\zeta^k -1} = 0
